          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Remove the lid for the last 30 minutes and cook on high to reduce. A teaspoon of cornflour mixed with cold water and stirred in also thickens quickly",
              "cause": "Tinned tomatoes released a lot of water",
              "symptom": "Sauce too thin"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Always brown sausages first. The caramelised exterior is part of the finished texture. Raw sausages that go in pale come out soft and lacking flavour",
              "cause": "Not browned before the slow cooker",
              "symptom": "Sausages very pale and soft"
            },
            {
              "fix": "The flavour of a sausage casserole depends heavily on the sausages. Higher-pork-content sausages (80% and above) produce a richer result than cheap brands",
              "cause": "The sausages were low quality",
              "symptom": "Casserole tastes flat"
